#Text=Andrea on her road to modeling , and America 's Next Top Model
#Text=MH : Who were the people you looked up to and inspired you to pursue modeling ?
#Text=Did they have that thin body type that you hoped to have ?
#Text=AM : I looked up to anyone in a media image as well as , and especially , America 's Next Top Model contestants .
#Text=MH : That was actually going to be my next question .
#Text=Who did you look up to on that show ?
#Text=AM : All the contestants on the show , minus the plus size girl because I knew modelling was all about thin and not regular people
#Text=MH : Some of the plus sized girls on that show actually went into rather lucrative careers , like Toccara from Cycle 3 , probably more so than some of the thinner winners .
#Text=How do you feel about that , and how would you have felt about such an event occurring before you overcame your anorexia ?
#Text=AM :
#Text=Like most of the viewers of the show , I had no idea where any of the winners or past-contestants ended up .
#Text=Now , I am starting to rebuild my career more than anyone ever helped me to before ... and to boot ...
#Text=I am healthy doing it .
#Text=MH : Definitely .
#Text=On that note , do you feel there is such a thing as " perfect " in terms of image in fashion ?
#Text=AM : Absolutely not in real life .
#Text=In the fashion world the perfect image is definitely " thin " and it will be for a long time to come .
#Text=MH : Even with the Toccaras and Tyra Banks of the world ?
#Text=AM :
#Text=Tyra Banks started off extremely thin to get to where she is today , I was sick and dying and not able to do the same .
#Text=Besides , look at the hype and criticism Tyra is getting for her present size and even Britney Spears for that matter .
#Text=MH : That is true .
#Text=Do you think Tyra Banks picks the bigger models for " good TV " instead of actually succeeding in modeling ?
#Text=AM : Absolutely - has any of them ever won yet ? ... or come close ?
#Text=MH : There was a big hype over Tyra picking Whitney and Diana for ANTM 8 , which was the first time two plus sized girls made it into the final rounds .
#Text=They were both eliminated midway through the competition .
#Text=That year Jaslene won .
#Text=Do you think her look is unhealthy in terms of how it 's promoted to the public and young girls ?
#Text=AM : Yes I do .
#Text=Look at me and how I looked when I won .
#Text=I could not even face the young children that I used to babysit on my crescent , let alone the whole world .
#Text=I was ashamed at how I looked .
#Text=MH :
#Text=Do you believe the producers for shows such as Top Model intentionally pick people who are perhaps unstable , whether it be with body image or otherwise ?
